We can simulate the circular array by traversing it twice.

Instead of creating another array,

Loop from

2*n - 1

down to

0

Use

i % n

to get the real index.

Maintain a Monotonic Decreasing Stack.

The stack stores values.

Before processing the current element:

Remove all elements smaller than or equal to it.
The remaining top (if any) is the next greater element.
