4. Algorithm

Let

n = nums.length

Create

answer[n]

Create an empty stack.

Traverse

for (i = 2*n - 1; i >= 0; i--)

For each element:

Current index

idx = i % n

While stack is not empty and

stack.peek() <= nums[idx]

Pop the stack.

If

i < n

Then

stack empty → answer = -1
otherwise → answer = stack.peek()

Push

nums[idx]
